<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-BCC9587C-6BB1-4F39-B62E-EC26DEDE7859" version="1" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-BCC9587C-6BB1-4F39-B62E-EC26DEDE7859" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">Clean the ruler</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-BBB42397-F195-4C1D-AD4B-FE798E61F9EA"><p class="- topic/p "> The printer uses a ruler to control the printhead carriage. A polluted ruler interferes with control of the printhead carriage. In case of pollution, you can clean the ruler. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Video: <ph class="- topic/ph " varid="Video: 20 - Clean the ruler"><xref class="- topic/xref " format="html" href="https://sus.cpp.canon/5XU5PS6Z" scope="external"><?ditaot usertext?><image class="- topic/image " href="GUID-1B93C780-C233-4810-947C-7EC17F913975-low.png" placement="inline" otherprops="GUID-1B93C780-C233-4810-947C-7EC17F913975-low.png"/>Clean the ruler</xref></ph>. 
</p><note class="- topic/note " id="GUID-DA9FD4B7-A637-4631-A74A-896E1EFD9719" type="note"><p class="- topic/p ">You can clean a ruler marked with a green dot. Do not clean a ruler that is not marked with a green dot. 
</p><fig class="- topic/fig " id="d38775e28"><image class="- topic/image " href="GUID-D50BE18D-0D61-4CF4-A0C1-CF83E7135F3C-low.png" placement="inline" otherprops="GUID-D50BE18D-0D61-4CF4-A0C1-CF83E7135F3C-low.png"/></fig></note></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">User task</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><context id="GUID-C5C6FCE7-880B-4138-989C-473D8898FB47" class="- topic/section task/context "><p class="- topic/p "> If the operator panel shows error 
<msgph class="+ topic/ph sw-d/msgph ">5709</msgph>, clean the ruler. 
</p></context><prereq id="GUID-223462BE-E8A6-42A4-8092-4911769DD50E" class="- topic/section task/prereq "><p class="- topic/p ">Use <ph varid="productname" class="- topic/ph ">Colorado M-Series</ph> prescribed: 
</p><ul id="UL_88FE82F1C6B343028F9B61DB8C430ED7" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_F4B9AC154F1445FBAA8F889824E6FD43" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><ph translate="no" class="- topic/ph ">Microflex</ph> gloves for handling ink 
</p></li><li id="LI_6FA5A3A7E0FE4587B6D4539C231C8B45" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Lint free cloths 
</p></li><li id="LI_5B59A09BD0644EBC948C0AA0C29B286B" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Cleaning liquid IPA 
</p></li></ul><note id="GUID-153CC759-3960-41C2-B43D-821B59856AAF" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">For information on the prescribed maintenance materials. 
</p></note></prereq><section id="GUID-C02D66D1-E3CC-4BC2-95F8-775D93D93431" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Warning / Caution</title><note type="caution" id="GUID-A97040BC-F110-4E4B-9CFF-E8082B9DA00E" class="- topic/note "><fig id="GUID-9848D934-FF3E-4AC9-BA07-69028FA44036" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-FCF86E23-0DD4-40BC-ACDF-FF8ABA1E6502-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-FCF86E23-0DD4-40BC-ACDF-FF8ABA1E6502-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">Avoid skin contact with ink: wear protective gloves. 
</p><fig id="GUID-7C716739-2AD7-42F8-8EF6-B28A8E7B1F76" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-D8099BBE-C3A2-4392-8B56-C532EDDD6073-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-D8099BBE-C3A2-4392-8B56-C532EDDD6073-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p "> Protect your eyes from splashing ink: wear safety glasses. 
</p></note></section><section id="SECTION_63E3642B0DFF489CBCD0BC953A812225" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "/><note id="GUID-CCB5C4A9-26C8-4DCC-BB44-A7F01347DB81" class="- topic/note " type="caution"><p class="- topic/p "> Wear gloves when contact with ink or maintenance materials is possible. Gloves should always overlap sleeves. Wear safety glasses with side shields when handling ink or maintenance materials. Follow the ink related Safety Data Sheets (SDS) guidelines carefully in order to ensure maximum safety. 
</p></note><note id="GUID-59B88697-ABFB-48A8-9C28-85FF1BEA5EEA" class="- topic/note " type="important"><p class="- topic/p "> Use the prescribed cleaning liquid. Do not use any other cleaners. 
</p></note></section><steps id="GUID-CBD6ADF1-6FC4-411E-A89A-E4C4292E3064" class="- topic/ol task/steps "><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Open the top cover of the printer. 
</cmd></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Put on the <ph varid="productname" class="- topic/ph ">Colorado M-Series</ph> approved gloves. 
</cmd></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Dampen a lint free cloth with the cleaner IPA and clean the left side of the ruler until you reach the printhead carriage. Make sure that the lint free cloth covers the front and back of the ruler. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig id="GUID-8B846B2F-980D-4CFE-8662-8A0D2D4DA099" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-13CCF065-A792-4959-9C2B-3DFEBD09BF87-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-13CCF065-A792-4959-9C2B-3DFEBD09BF87-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Close the top cover. 
</cmd></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd "> Start the maintenance action via the operator panel. Make sure that the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "><text class="- topic/text ">Automatic nozzle optimization</text></uicontrol> is deselected. 
</cmd></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Wait until the printhead carriage is in cleaning position. 
</cmd></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Open the top cover. 
</cmd></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Dampen a lint free cloth with the cleaner IPA and clean the right-hand side of the ruler. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig id="GUID-72D26A82-AA5C-48AA-960B-951C50FD67AA" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-E207FFA7-D0C5-4374-8F2B-8C2114F248E2-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-E207FFA7-D0C5-4374-8F2B-8C2114F248E2-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd "> Dispose the gloves and cloths as chemical waste according to local regulations. 
</cmd></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Close the top cover. 
</cmd></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">On the operator panel, tap <ph class="- topic/ph "><uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "><text class="- topic/text ">Completed</text></uicontrol></ph> to end the maintenance action. 
</cmd></step></steps></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-412C614D-9E31-4E8D-B644-52D11B3C77FC.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>User task</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
</task>